KAIZER Chiefs have confirmed their 18-man squad for the upcoming Caf Champions League group-stage clash with Moroccan giants Wydad Casablanca. Amakhosi started their group C campaign with a goalless draw against Guinean outfit Horoya at FNB Stadium on Tuesday. Now they face Moroccan giants in a match that was initially scheduled to be played on 13 February in Morocco, but was postponed. Chiefs will now face Wydad in a neutral venue, at 4 August Stadium in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso on Sunday, 6pm. Coach Gavin Hunt announced a 18-man squad that will travel in a special chartered flight on Friday. Chiefs 18 Man Squad for Wydad Casablanca Clash Goalkeepers:Daniel Akpeyi, Itumeleng KhuneDefenders:Daniel Cardoso, Reeve Frosler, Ramahlwe Mphahlele, Siyabonga Ngezana, Philani Zulu, Anthony AgayMidfielders:Njabulo Blom, Darrel Matsheke, Willard Katsande, Nkosingiphile Ngcobo, Lebogang Manyama, Kearyn BaccusForwards:Lazalous Kambole, Samir Nurkovic, Bernard Parker, Leonardo Castro   